<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Growth refers to the increase in colony activities and population expansion up to the time of the summer solstice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUMMER SOLSTICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Summer solstice marks the peak of colony activities and population expansion before the shift towards winter preparations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 80}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 137}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY ACTIVITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Colony activities include population expansion and nectar and pollen collection, which are the main focus until the summer solstice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR AND POLLEN COLLECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar and pollen collection are key activities during the early season, primarily aimed at population expansion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER PREPARATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter preparation involves reducing brood rearing and building up stores of honey, starting after the summer solstice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD REARING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood rearing is a continuous activity throughout the season, but it tapers off as the focus shifts to winter preparation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 79}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey production is a significant activity for beekeepers, representing the bees' stored honey for winter."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey production is the process of producing honey by the bees."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 48}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 119}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POPULATION DROP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Population drop occurs with the onset of autumn, reflecting a decrease in colony activities and brood rearing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AUTUMN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SEASON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Autumn is characterized by a slowing down of activities in the hive, with less frenetic movement and more time spent in clusters."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLUSTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cluster refers to the bees huddling together to maintain the brood nest at approximately 94°F (34°C), especially as nights begin to cool."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 80}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 135}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;94°F (34°C)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TEMPERATURE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The temperature of the brood nest must be maintained at approximately 94°F (34°C) year-round to ensure the survival of the brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DAYS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Days refer to the length of daylight, which changes after the summer solstice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bees are a group of insects that are managed by beekeepers and are central to the discussion about beekeeping activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are social insects that perform dances to communicate the location of food sources to their hivemates."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the individual members of the hive who perform various roles such as foraging, processing, and communicating."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the main subjects of the text, performing various activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees refer to the honeybees that perform the natural behavior of swarming."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees refer to the individual insects that make up the honey bee colony, working together to maintain the colony's functions and activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees refer to the insects that form colonies and can move into various locations, including hollow trees, chimneys, and walls."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-639b82447dffe6728b40a209919fad7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49ee09b3db57739dfa10e0ec383b5a4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-817bec40e1f316234277157c4faca623&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 42}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 113}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Hive is the structure where bees live and store honey and pollen, and it is the primary focus of beekeeping activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the central structure where bees live and perform their dances to communicate with each other."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the central structure where bees live, process nectar, and communicate through dances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the living space of the bee colony where bees live, store food, and raise brood."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the location where bees live and communicate the location of nectar sources to other members of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where bees process nectar into honey, involving both forager and house bees in the process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where the bees live and perform their activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where the colony lives, containing the brood nest and storage areas for honey and pollen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hiving is the process of capturing a wild colony and placing it in a hive, which can be challenging and requires skill."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Hive is the central location from which bees operate and perform dances to communicate information about food sources."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49ee09b3db57739dfa10e0ec383b5a4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-817bec40e1f316234277157c4faca623&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0cf0b37864347226f145a22592586fb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 42}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 114}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADULT POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adult Population refers to the worker bees in a honeybee colony responsible for maintaining the brood nest and other tasks."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adult population refers to the mature bees that form the cluster and maintain the brood nest."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD NEST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Nest is the area within the hive where the queen lays her eggs and the young bees develop until they emerge as adults."&lt;SEP&gt;"Brood nest is the area in the hive where the bees raise their young."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADULT BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adult bees are the mature bees that form the cluster and maintain the brood nest."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NIGHTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nights refer to the periods of darkness, which begin to cool as autumn approaches."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRENETIC PACE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Frenetic pace describes the rapid activity level of the bees during the early season."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STORES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"RESOURCE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stores are the honey and other resources the bees collect and store for winter."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADULT BEES' CLUSTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adult bees' cluster is the group of adult bees that huddle together to maintain warmth."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-40cf406bb36c51a3bb8a0a3ea130031e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OVERCROWDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Overcrowding is a condition that can lead to swarming, as the colony becomes too dense and resources are strained."&lt;SEP&gt;"Overcrowding is a condition that can lead to swarming, as the colony becomes too dense and resources are strained."|&gt;&lt;7</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Bee is the reproductive female bee that lays eggs and maintains the colony within the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Bee is the reproductive female in the colony responsible for laying eggs and maintaining the genetic continuity of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 123}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A colony is a group of honey bees living together in a hive, managed by a beekeeper."&lt;SEP&gt;"A colony refers to a group of bees living together in a hive, which has survived at least one winter and is preparing for a new year starting around mid-March."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony is a group of bees living together, performing various tasks to maintain the hive and ensure survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony is the group of bees living together within the hive, performing various activities such as foraging and dancing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to a group of bees living together in a hive, managed by beekeepers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to a group of honeybees living together in a hive, including the queen, workers, and drones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25b63504237ee11d327b37a8abd236b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 123}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPRING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Spring is a season characterized by the beginning of the active season for beekeeping, when new activities start."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spring is mentioned as the time when the hive is first opened, indicating the start of the beekeeper's year."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spring is the season when truckload shipments of package bees are arranged and shipped."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spring marks the beginning of a new year for the honey bee colony, typically around mid-March, when population and activity levels start to increase."&lt;SEP&gt;"Spring marks the beginning of the active breeding and expansion phase of the honeybee colony, characterized by increased egg-laying and resource collection."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0a8c416dc0695d5c1e06f3541ce9ffc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 79}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWARMING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swarming is a natural process where a large number of bees leave the original colony to form a new one, often due to overcrowding or other stress factors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESOURCE STRAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Resource Strain is a factor that can contribute to swarming, as the colony lacks sufficient resources to support its population."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by flowers that bees collect to make honey and feed the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is the raw material collected by foragers and processed by house bees to make honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is the resource collected by Field Bees and processed by House Bees, crucial for the survival and productivity of the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is the sweet liquid produced by flowers that foragers collect and communicate the location of using dances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"RESOURCE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollen is a fine powder produced by plants that bees collect to provide protein and other nutrients to the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is another resource collected by Field Bees, often mentioned alongside nectar in the context of foraging activities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drones are male bees in the colony whose primary function is to mate with the queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DAY LENGTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Day Length is a factor that influences the queen's egg-laying behavior and the colony's activities, particularly during the transition from fall to spring."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LATITUDE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Latitude is a geographical coordinate that affects the timing of the queen stopping egg-laying and the subsequent swarming behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MANAGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Management refers to the actions taken by beekeepers to control swarming and maintain the health of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Management refers to the overall care and supervision of the bee colony, including tasks like feeding, cleaning, and monitoring."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25b63504237ee11d327b37a8abd236b3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 11}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 72}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeping is the practice of keeping bees, typically for the production of honey or for pollination services, involving various challenges and uncertainties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping is the practice of keeping honeybees for the production of honey, pollination services, or other benefits."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping is the practice of managing and caring for bee colonies, involving various aspects such as time, cost, and restrictions."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping refers to the practice of raising honey bees, which involves various activities such as learning, managing hives, and visiting bees regularly."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4ff0d3047b19e50793ea40860c34e98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 48}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 118}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTROL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Control is a concept that is challenged during the process of First Contact."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Control is a strategy used by beekeepers to manage swarming, often involving splitting the colony or reducing the queen's egg-laying."&lt;SEP&gt;"Control refers to the ability to manage and predict outcomes in beekeeping, which is limited due to the presence of many variables."&lt;SEP&gt;"Control refers to the ability to manage or govern, which is challenged by an intelligence that writes its own rules."&lt;SEP&gt;"Control refers to the power to direct or influence the management or policies of an organization."&lt;SEP&gt;"The concept of Control is challenged by the Intelligence that writes its own rules."|</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2c97437b365f5eb5e2f2cc5e0ff5a3ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2c467c9c1615ef14955cef413b8612d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e5759c1eccdacad5abbaa5faf9975ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25b63504237ee11d327b37a8abd236b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aabc464002a4ba146a5fb5107b31b72c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f5291955ed514f3c0e0eb381e9616fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0cec3a21355fd6b2067ed1d10efa62b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY HEALTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Colony Health refers to the overall well-being of the colony, including the balance of worker bees, drones, and the queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EGG-LAYING RATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Egg-Laying Rate is the number of eggs the queen lays per day, which increases as the colony prepares for spring."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW YEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New Year marks the beginning of a new cycle of colony growth and activity, driven by the availability of resources and the queen's egg-laying."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CYCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cycle refers to the recurring pattern of colony growth, egg-laying, and swarming that occurs throughout the year."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Colony Growth is the process by which the colony expands in size and activity, particularly during the spring and summer months."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e1f7470b2085ff42cc6a9b6fc4d481c2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SARS-COV-2&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"SARS-CoV-2 is a virus that caused the COVID-19 pandemic, impacting various governmental and organizational responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ce5aa51341a68f00646554cc0dce9a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 40}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COVID-19&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"COVID-19 is a specific strain of SARS-CoV-2, causing a global health crisis and prompting governmental and organizational responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5ce5aa51341a68f00646554cc0dce9a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNITED STATES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
