<node id="&quot;HOUSE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"House Bees are responsible for processing nectar into honey within the hive, evaluating the quality of incoming nectar loads."&lt;SEP&gt;"House Bees are responsible for processing the nectar brought back by Field Bees and are aware of the quality of the nectar."&lt;SEP&gt;"House bees are the group of bees that stay within the hive to perform various tasks such as caring for brood, building comb, and processing honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
