</node>
<node id="&quot;INSECTICIDE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CHEMICAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Insecticide is a chemical used to kill insects, which can disrupt the colony's activities and affect the lifespan of bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEWLY EMERGED YOUNG BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Newly emerged young bees are potential nurse bees that can be killed by insecticides, leading to a quick maturation of older bees to fill in the gap."&lt;SEP&gt;"Newly emerged young bees, also known as potential nurse bees, are affected by the presence of insecticides in the pollen cells."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
