<node id="&quot;WINTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter is a period of low activity and population in the honey bee colony due to reduced forage availability and colder temperatures."&lt;SEP&gt;"Winter is a period when the colony's population decreases."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Winter is a season during which beekeeping activities can be affected, with shorter and less frequent visits possible."&lt;SEP&gt;"Winter is a season when beekeeping activities are reduced, but hives still require attention."</data>
