<node id="&quot;MONOD AND JACOB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Monod and Jacob are mentioned as examples of scientists who found situations where the rules of regulation have been broken, similar to Rowley."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod and Jacob are scientists known for pioneering the enzyme regulation system that Varmus studied at NIH."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod and Jacob are scientists known for studying constitutive mutants, which are always active."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod and Jacob are scientists whose work on enzyme regulation systems inspired Varmus's research at NIH."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod and Jacob refer to scientists known for their work in breaking the rules of regulation and investigating the consequences, setting a precedent for Janet Rowley's approach."</data>
