<node id="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Viral oncogenes are genes found in tumor viruses that can cause cancer in animals, derived from normal cellular genes called proto-oncogenes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cellular proto-oncogenes are normal genes in cells that can become oncogenes under certain conditions, often due to mutations, and are found in both animals and humans."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}]</data>
</node>
