<node id="&quot;MIX/BELT VOCAL PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNIQUE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mix/Belt Vocal Production is a technique used by both males and females in music theater, though men typically use it higher in their vocal range, at the secondo passaggio."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mix/belt vocal production is a combination of classical and belt singing techniques used in musical performances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mix/belt vocal production is a technique used in music theater, combining elements of both chest and head voice registers to produce a powerful and versatile sound."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0267286c81e05982bbb46c95364cbb30&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb2da1f90d8529348f68db024bb17056&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569</data>
