<node id="&quot;MALE PASSAGGIO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Male passaggio is a pivotal point in the male vocal range where the registration shifts from chest to head register, typically occurring around C4–E4."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 100}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECONDO PASSAGGIO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Secondo passaggio is an Italian term referring to the high male passaggio, a crucial point in the male vocal range where the voice transitions from chest to head register."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 55}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 128}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHEST REGISTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chest register is a lower vocal register characterized by a fuller, more resonant sound, often associated with a warmer timbre."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 100}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEAD REGISTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Head register is a higher vocal register characterized by a brighter, more focused sound, often associated with a clearer and more piercing timbre."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 100}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL TRACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Tract is the resonator that shapes the sound produced by the vocal folds, contributing to the color, timbre, and resonance of the voice."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal tract is the pathway through which air travels from the lungs to the larynx and out of the mouth or nose, affecting the quality of the sound produced."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLASSICAL MALE SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNIQUE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Classical male singing involves techniques that darken, modify, or 'cover' the pitches in the passaggio range to achieve a specific sound quality."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 100}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPEAKING VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNIQUE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Speaking Voice involves optimizing frequency range, breath, intensity, rate, and resonance for effective communication."&lt;SEP&gt;"Speaking voice is the natural vocal production used in everyday conversation, often serving as the foundation for various singing techniques."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59e10c7e6d1073196e6649875ab91569&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
