<node id="&quot;BREATH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Breath is the air used to power the vocal folds during speech."&lt;SEP&gt;"Breath is the power source that sets the vocal folds in motion, essential for singing and requiring more oxygen than speech."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Folds are the delicate structures responsible for producing voice and require adequate lubrication to function efficiently."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal Folds are the primary sound-producing structures in the larynx, essential for singing and speaking."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal Folds are the vibrators that produce sound when set in motion by the breath, crucial for the production of the singing voice."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal folds are the primary components of the vocal mechanism responsible for producing sound through vibration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a51071d5167d43f8855eef4ba001dbe8</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 83}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 141}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foragers collect nectar and bring it back to the hive, passing it off to house bees for further processing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;E5&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"E5 is a specific vocal range that females are taking their mix/belt singing up to, indicating a high level of skill."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOPICAL POLITICAL AND SOCIAL ISSUES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Topical Political and Social Issues were addressed by rock musicals of the 1960s, reflecting the cultural and societal changes of that era."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OXYGEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Oxygen is required for singing, which demands more oxygen than speech, highlighting the physical demands of this vocal technique."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 98}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTROLLED EXHALE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Controlled Exhale is necessary for singing, requiring a longer and more controlled exhale than speaking, emphasizing the importance of breath control."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 98}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Resonance is the quality of the voice that is shaped by the vocal tract, contributing to the color, timbre, and overall sound of the singing voice."&lt;SEP&gt;"Resonance is the quality of the voice that makes it sound full and rich."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 98}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Color refers to the tonal quality of the voice, which is influenced by the vocal tract and contributes to the overall sound of the singing voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 98}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIMBRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Timbre is the unique quality of the voice that distinguishes it from others, shaped by the vocal tract and contributing to the overall sound of the singing voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 98}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIELD BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Field Bees are responsible for collecting nectar and bringing it back to the hive, and they are evaluated based on the quality of the nectar they bring."&lt;SEP&gt;"Field Bees are responsible for collecting nectar and bringing it back to the hive, passing it off to house bees for further processing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b</data>
