</node>
<node id="&quot;LOAD OF NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Load of Nectar is the amount of nectar collected by foragers and passed to house bees for processing into honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCOUT BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Scout Bee is a type of bee that searches for new sources of high-quality nectar and communicates this information to the hive through a dance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW SOURCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New Source is a newly discovered location of high-quality nectar that Scout Bees find and communicate to the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPOLIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Propolis is a resin-like substance collected by bees for various hive maintenance tasks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Water is a resource collected by bees for hive maintenance and cooling purposes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POTENTIAL HOMESITE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Potential Homesite is a location that Scout Bees search for and communicate to the hive as a possible new home for the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANCE LANGUAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dance Language is the method used by bees to communicate information about resources and locations within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b4a89506d188c7f38e0a99c881431e3b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVEMATES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hivemates are the members of the bee colony who receive and act on information communicated through dances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hivemates are the other bees in the hive that receive and interpret the dances performed by foragers."</data>
