</node>
<node id="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Wag-Tail Dance is a specific type of dance performed by bees to signal the discovery of a new nectar source more than 100 meters from the hive. It conveys both the distance and direction of the source with high precision."&lt;SEP&gt;"Wag-Tail Dance is another type of dance used by foragers to signal new foraging locations, typically for distances beyond 100 meters."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Forager is a term used to describe a bee that has found a new food source and returns to the hive to communicate its location."&lt;SEP&gt;"Forager is a term used to describe a bee that searches for nectar sources and conveys information back to the hive through a figure-eight pattern."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0cf0b37864347226f145a22592586fb</data>
