</node>
<node id="&quot;MYELOGENOUS LEUKEMIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Myelogenous leukemia is a type of blood cancer characterized by the abnormal proliferation of myeloid cells in the bone marrow."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a1794c4fa3680656aaab5d3de43949e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BCR/ABL PROTEIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROTEIN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The bcr/abl protein is a hybrid protein produced by the fusion of the _bcr_ and _abl_ genes, which has abnormally elevated activity and disrupts cell regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a1794c4fa3680656aaab5d3de43949e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CML&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DISEASE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"CML stands for Chronic Myelogenous Leukemia, a specific form of myelogenous leukemia where the normal control of white cell multiplication is disrupted by the mutant bcr/abl protein."</data>
