  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foragers convey information about nectar sources to the hive through a figure-eight pattern."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d0cf0b37864347226f145a22592586fb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee is the reproductive female of the colony and maintains the colony's activities."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A package is introduced to a colony to strengthen or expand it."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7c6b4aa8d243f96f198f44c125be2f03</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;NUCLEUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A nucleus is used to start a new colony, including a queen and worker bees."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7c6b4aa8d243f96f198f44c125be2f03</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGING FORCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The foraging force is a part of the colony responsible for gathering resources, and its disruption can lead to a rapid maturation of house bees to replace foragers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;HOUSE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"House bees are essential members of the colony, performing tasks such as caring for brood and maintaining the hive, and their activities can be disrupted by external factors like insecticides."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;INSECTICIDE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Insecticide can cause a massive disruption in the colony by wiping out the foraging force and affecting the overall balance of activities within the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;PROPERTY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A property can host a bee colony, providing a suitable environment for the bees to thrive."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">26.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A beekeeper is responsible for managing and caring for a bee colony, ensuring its survival and productivity."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeepers manage colonies of honey bees, ensuring their health and well-being."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;MID-MARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mid-March signifies the start of a new year for the colony, marking the beginning of increased activity and new life."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;NEW LIFE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"New life within the colony is a sign of increased activity and growth, which is an important aspect of the colony's cycle."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The population of the colony fluctuates throughout the year, with a low point during winter and a high point as new life emerges."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE MANAGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hive management is the act of maintaining and managing the colony."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey bees live and work together in a colony, performing tasks necessary for the survival and growth of the group."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeepers are responsible for managing the colony, ensuring its health and productivity."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-25b63504237ee11d327b37a8abd236b3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;CHORE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chores performed by beekeepers, such as opening the hive, can significantly impact the colony's life."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-25b63504237ee11d327b37a8abd236b3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance is performed by members of the colony to communicate the precise location of nectar sources."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Round Dance is performed by members of the colony to communicate the location of nectar sources within 100 meters of the hive."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Forager Bees are part of the colony and perform foraging activities to discover nectar sources."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;WORKER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Worker Bees are part of the colony and perform various activities such as foraging and dancing."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;DRONE BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Drone Bees are part of the colony and mate with the queen."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;SUNLIGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sunlight is important for the colony as it helps bees perform the Wag-Tail Dance accurately."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;BEESWAX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beeswax is essential for the construction of the honeycomb, which supports the colony's activities."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGING ACTIVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foraging Activity is an essential activity performed by the colony to collect nectar and pollen."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;COMMUNICATION ACTIVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Communication Activity is an essential activity performed by the colony to ensure effective communication of information."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;RANDOM SEARCH ACTIVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Random Search Activity is an essential activity performed by the colony to locate nectar sources within the 100-meter radius."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;PRECISION INFORMATION CONVEYANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Precision Information Conveyance is an essential activity performed by the colony to ensure accurate communication of nectar source information."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SPRING&quot;" target="&quot;POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"In spring, the rate of population growth increases due to lengthening days, warmer weather, and blooming plants."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7c6b4aa8d243f96f198f44c125be2f03</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SPRING&quot;" target="&quot;NEW BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"New bees emerge from the brood, increasing the population."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7c6b4aa8d243f96f198f44c125be2f03</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SPRING&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"In Spring, the honey bee colony begins a new year with increased activity and population as the weather improves and forage becomes available."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SPRING&quot;" target="&quot;ACTIVE SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Spring marks the start of the active season for beekeeping, when more frequent visits to the hives are required."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SPRING&quot;" target="&quot;TRUCKLOAD SHIPMENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Truckload Shipments are arranged and shipped during the Spring season."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-c0a8c416dc0695d5c1e06f3541ce9ffc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NECTAR&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foragers collect nectar, which is then processed by house bees, showing the origin of the raw material."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NECTAR&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foragers collect Nectar and use dances to communicate its location to other bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MANAGEMENT&quot;" target="&quot;CHORE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">91.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chores, such as opening the hive, are part of the broader management of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-25b63504237ee11d327b37a8abd236b3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;TIME&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeeping requires a certain amount of time, which can vary depending on the level of involvement and experience of the beekeeper."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;COST&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeeping involves costs such as equipment, maintenance, and possibly hiring additional help, which can vary based on the scale of the operation."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;RESTRICTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeeping can be restrictive in terms of space, time, and resources required, affecting the beekeeper's lifestyle and other commitments."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeeping provides the opportunity to produce honey, which is one of the main benefits of beekeeping."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;POLLINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeeping contributes to pollination, which is another important benefit of beekeeping, helping to maintain plant biodiversity."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;LEARNING PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The learning period is a crucial part of beekeeping, during which the beekeeper gains the necessary skills and knowledge to manage the bees."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;VISITING BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Regular visits to the bees are an integral part of the beekeeping process."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;" target="&quot;HOBBY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeeping is engaged in as a hobby, expecting it to initially cost money rather than generate profit."</data>
