  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERMITS&quot;" target="&quot;PERMITTED ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">121.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Permits are a type of regulatory requirement that can be subject to encumbrances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Permits can be subject to encumbrances as defined in the document."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PERMITTED ENCUMBRANCE&quot;" target="&quot;CONCEPT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Permitted Encumbrance is a specific type of obligation mentioned in the document."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;STOCK EXCHANGE&quot;" target="&quot;ORGANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Stock Exchange is a location or organization where financial transactions occur."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TAXES&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Taxes are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ASSESSMENTS&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Assessments are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LANDLORDS'&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Landlords' are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CARRIERS'&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Carriers' are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAREHOUSEMEN'S&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Warehousemen's are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MECHANICS'&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mechanics' are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPAIRMEN'S&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Repairmen's are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WORKERS'&quot;" target="&quot;ENCUMBRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Workers' are a form of encumbrance that can be contested or not yet due."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-37a075765fb0e7608ba2effbe18b9c3c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIP ORDERS&quot;" target="&quot;DEBTORS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">72.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Debtors must comply with the DIP Orders related to financing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors must not be in default under the DIP Orders, subject to any applicable grace and cure periods."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5f512e8664aea56aafd9fad806cbfc40&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d74d1f34ad557a505f7269db12d4c6eb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIP ORDERS&quot;" target="&quot;SUPPORTING LENDERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Supporting Lenders must ensure that the Debtors comply with the DIP Orders."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d74d1f34ad557a505f7269db12d4c6eb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIP ORDERS&quot;" target="&quot;BANKRUPTCY COURT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">36.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bankruptcy Court must oversee the implementation of the DIP Orders."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d74d1f34ad557a505f7269db12d4c6eb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HEALTH&quot;" target="&quot;CHORE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">84.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chores, such as opening the hive, are necessary for maintaining the health of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-25b63504237ee11d327b37a8abd236b3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL LAWS&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeepers must adhere to Environmental Laws to ensure responsible beekeeping practices."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-49ee09b3db57739dfa10e0ec383b5a4e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;INSECTICIDE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Insecticide affects the lifespan of bees, particularly young bees, by causing their death if ingested."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">45.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees perform dances to communicate the discovery of nectar sources to other bees."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;NECTAR SOURCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">45.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees discover nectar sources and communicate their location to other bees through dances."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">40.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Forager Bees are a subset of bees that specifically collect nectar from discovered sources."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;SUN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">35.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The orientation of the figure-eight pattern in the Wag-Tail Dance is related to the direction of the sun."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;FIGURE-EIGHT PATTERN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">40.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use the Figure-Eight Pattern in the Wag-Tail Dance to convey information about the nectar source."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;DISTANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use dances to convey the distance to nectar sources, with the Wag-Tail Dance providing more precise information."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;DIRECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use dances to convey the direction to nectar sources, with the Wag-Tail Dance providing more precise information."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;SAMPLE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use samples of nectar or pollen during the Round Dance to indicate the type of forage discovered."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;ODOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use odors adhering to their bodies during the Round Dance to indicate the type of forage discovered."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;PRECISION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance provides more precise information than the Round Dance, conveying both distance and direction."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;MARGIN OF ERROR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance conveys information within a relatively small margin of error, making it more accurate than the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;RANDOM SEARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees perform a random search within the 100-meter radius indicated by the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;COLLECTING NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Forager Bees collect nectar from the discovered sources and return to the Hive to perform dances."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;COMMUNICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">36.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dances such as the Round Dance and Wag-Tail Dance are used by bees to communicate the discovery of nectar sources to other bees."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEE&quot;" target="&quot;INFORMATION CONVEYED&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dances like the Round Dance and Wag-Tail Dance convey specific information about nectar sources, including distance and direction."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ACTIVE SEASON&quot;" target="&quot;OFF SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The active season affects the lifespan of bees more than the off season."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ACTIVE SEASON&quot;" target="&quot;VISITING BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"During the active season, beekeepers visit their hives more frequently to manage the colonies effectively."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9d1126dbefe50ca8882a75d7e639c94c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOUSE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"House bees process nectar brought by foragers, indicating a clear workflow and collaboration within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOUSE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;FIELD BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">30.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"House bees process nectar brought by field bees, indicating a clear workflow and collaboration within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSECTICIDE&quot;" target="&quot;NEWLY EMERGED YOUNG BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Insecticides can cause the death of newly emerged young bees, which are potential nurse bees, leading to a quick maturation of older bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSECTICIDE&quot;" target="&quot;POLLEN FORAGERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pollen foragers can inadvertently bring insecticides back to the hive, which can affect the health and lifespan of young bees stored in pollen cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSECTICIDE&quot;" target="&quot;STORED IN POLLEN CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Insecticides can affect bees stored in pollen cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEWLY EMERGED YOUNG BEES&quot;" target="&quot;OLDER BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">21.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Older bees can quickly graduate and take up foraging roles to replace the lost foragers, and some of them may also develop faster to fill in for the departing older ones."&lt;SEP&gt;"Older bees help restore the balance in the hive by secreting brood food after the loss of young bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEWLY EMERGED YOUNG BEES&quot;" target="&quot;INSECTICIDES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Insecticides cause the death of newly emerged young bees as they feed on stored pollen in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BROOD&quot;" target="&quot;YOUNG BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Young bees can pass quickly through the phase of brood secretion to wax secretion based on the needs of the colony, and this capability can atrophy if there is little brood to raise."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BROOD&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Brood is part of the honey bee colony and gives off pheromones."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;POLLEN FORAGERS&quot;" target="&quot;INSECTICIDES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pollen foragers inadvertently bring back insecticides to the hive, which affects the young bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NURSE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;YOUNG BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Nurse bees are young bees that care for the brood, and their development can be affected by the presence of insecticides in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DEVELOPMENT PHASES&quot;" target="&quot;WAX SECRETION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">4.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Young bees pass through development phases, including wax secretion."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAX SECRETION&quot;" target="&quot;CARING FOR BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">3.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Caring for brood is a task performed by house bees during a specific development phase."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BUILDING COMB&quot;" target="&quot;PROCESSING HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">2.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Building comb and processing honey are tasks performed by house bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MASSIVE DISRUPTION&quot;" target="&quot;STORED IN POLLEN CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Massive disruption can affect bees stored in pollen cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5432dc0f860913abcd37f8b24e3bcc22</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OLDER BEES&quot;" target="&quot;PHEROMONES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pheromones signal the status and needs of life in the hive, prompting older bees to secrete brood food."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPER'S YEAR&quot;" target="&quot;BEE'S YEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The beekeeper's year overlaps with the bee's year but focuses on hive management rather than the natural cycle of activities within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;ADULTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Adult bees are part of the honey bee colony and give off pheromones."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;RELATIVE INACTIVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">23.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Relative Inactivity is a part of the honey bee colony's year-round activity pattern, where activity levels are lower but not completely halted."&lt;SEP&gt;"Relative inactivity is a period during the year when the honey bee colony's activity decreases."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;HIBERNATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hibernation does not occur in the honey bee colony, emphasizing continuous activity."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Seasons affect the type and level of activity in the honey bee colony throughout the year."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;CLIMATE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Climate affects the type and level of activity in the honey bee colony throughout the year."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;GEOGRAPHY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Geography affects the type and level of activity in the honey bee colony throughout the year."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a56afe52a888e5c4267f47f027e036</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;WINTER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"During Winter, the honey bee colony experiences low activity and population due to reduced forage availability and colder temperatures."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;SUMMER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"In Summer, the honey bee colony reaches its peak activity and population with abundant forage available."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;FALL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"In Fall, the honey bee colony prepares for Winter by reducing activity and population levels as forage becomes scarce."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;NORTH AMERICA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The annual population cycle of a honey bee colony in North America can vary based on local conditions such as climate and geography."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;YEAR-ROUND ACTIVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Year-Round Activity is a characteristic of the honey bee colony, which maintains a consistent level of activity even during periods of relative inactivity."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;ADEQUATE FOOD RESERVES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Adequate Food Reserves are crucial for the health and survival of the honey bee colony, especially during periods of low forage availability."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;NORMAL FORAGE AVAILABILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Normal Forage Availability supports the maintenance of a healthy honey bee colony, providing the necessary resources for population and activity levels."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;LOCAL VARIATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Local Variations affect the annual population cycle of the honey bee colony, reflecting differences based on specific geographic and environmental conditions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;SHORT-TERM VARIABILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Short-Term Variability in the honey bee colony's population and activity levels is influenced by immediate environmental conditions, reflecting the colony's adaptability."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;LOW POINT IN POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Low Point in Population occurs during late Winter, when the honey bee colony has the fewest bees due to reduced forage availability and colder temperatures."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;HIGH ACTIVITY LEVEL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"High Activity Level is experienced by the honey bee colony during Spring and Summer, when forage is abundant and the colony is most active."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;LOW ACTIVITY LEVEL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Low Activity Level is experienced by the honey bee colony during Winter and early Spring, when forage is scarce and activity levels are lower."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEE COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;POPULATION CYCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Population Cycle describes the fluctuation in the number of bees within the honey bee colony throughout the year, influenced by seasonal changes and environmental factors."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a40a756fcfe048bdd7aa9b2b44a0469e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WINTER&quot;" target="&quot;POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">13.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"During winter, the bee population decreases due to daily deaths and reduced brood rearing."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Winter is a period when the population of the colony decreases."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7c6b4aa8d243f96f198f44c125be2f03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2771339c1e811ad3b10c069322fcb0df</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WINTER&quot;" target="&quot;DIE-OFF&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"During winter, the rate of die-off increases, leading to a decrease in the bee population."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7c6b4aa8d243f96f198f44c125be2f03</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WINTER&quot;" target="&quot;VISITING BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
