  <data key="d6">chunk-d8f3462bc4bebbc27d5f13df929a9935</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SERENGETI RULES&quot;" target="&quot;HUMAN BIOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Serengeti Rules provide insights into ecological principles that are relevant to understanding the impacts of human biological activities, such as drug development and medical treatments."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SERENGETI RULES&quot;" target="&quot;CLINICAL TESTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Serengeti Rules highlight the importance of considering ecological factors in clinical tests, emphasizing the need to understand the broader environmental impacts of medical interventions."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SERENGETI RULES&quot;" target="&quot;ECOSYSTEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Serengeti Rules provide insights into the interconnectedness of species within ecosystems, highlighting the importance of maintaining these systems for the production of essential resources like clean air and water."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SERENGETI RULES&quot;" target="&quot;BIODIVERSITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Serengeti Rules emphasize the importance of biodiversity in maintaining healthy ecosystems, which is crucial for the survival of many species."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SERENGETI RULES&quot;" target="&quot;CLEAN AIR AND WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">36.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Serengeti Rules explain the connections among species that contribute to the production of clean air and water, which are essential natural resources."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SERENGETI RULES&quot;" target="&quot;REGULATORY AGENCIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Regulatory agencies are responsible for ensuring that the Serengeti Rules are considered in drug approval processes."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CLINICAL TESTS&quot;" target="&quot;DRUGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Clinical tests are crucial for ensuring that drugs are safe and effective, but they also underscore the need to consider the ecological impacts of these substances once they are released into the environment."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CLINICAL TESTS&quot;" target="&quot;REGULATORY AGENCIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">40.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Clinical tests are subject to oversight by regulatory agencies, which ensure that drugs meet safety and efficacy standards before approval."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CLINICAL TESTS&quot;" target="&quot;DOCTORS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Doctors play a critical role in clinical tests by prescribing and administering drugs to patients, and their expertise is essential for evaluating drug efficacy and safety."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CLINICAL TESTS&quot;" target="&quot;PATIENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Patients are the subjects of clinical tests, and their participation is necessary to evaluate the safety and efficacy of drugs before they are approved for use."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CLINICAL TESTS&quot;" target="&quot;SPECIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">30.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Clinical tests can have indirect impacts on species, particularly if the drugs being tested affect the populations of certain species or their habitats."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CLINICAL TESTS&quot;" target="&quot;MEDICAL CONDITION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">45.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Clinical tests evaluate the effectiveness of drugs in treating specific medical conditions, and the results of these tests inform drug approval processes."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;POPULATION BOOMED TO 7 BILLION&quot;" target="&quot;HABITAT DISTURBANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The rapid increase in human population has led to extensive habitat disturbance, affecting ecosystems and the species within them, including lions."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HUNTING, FISHING, FARMING, FORESTING, AND BURNING&quot;" target="&quot;HABITAT DISTURBANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"These human activities contribute to habitat disturbance, altering ecosystems and impacting the populations of various species, such as lions."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HABITAT DISTURBANCE&quot;" target="&quot;LIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Habitat disturbance caused by human activities threatens lion populations, disrupting their natural habitats and leading to declines in their numbers."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HABITAT DISTURBANCE&quot;" target="&quot;SPECIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">81.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Habitat disturbance can lead to declines in species populations, disrupting the balance of ecosystems."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Habitat disturbance caused by human activities can lead to declines in species populations, disrupting the balance of ecosystems."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HABITAT DISTURBANCE&quot;" target="&quot;CLEAN AIR AND WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">72.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Habitat disturbance can degrade the quality of air and water, affecting the production of clean air and water by ecosystems."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8c7ef5a137445787b9c383b31e287ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LIONS&quot;" target="&quot;TANZANIA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Lions are found in Tanzania, particularly in the Serengeti, highlighting the country's importance in preserving these animals."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LIONS&quot;" target="&quot;HUMANITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Humanity's population growth and resource exploitation have led to the significant decline in lion populations, affecting their habitats and survival."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LIONS&quot;" target="&quot;ECOSYSTEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Lions play a crucial role in maintaining the balance of ecosystems, and their decline can lead to 'sick' ecosystems."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ECOSYSTEMS&quot;" target="&quot;SHARKS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sharks are apex predators that help maintain the balance of marine ecosystems, and their decline can lead to 'sick' ecosystems."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ECOSYSTEMS&quot;" target="&quot;GLOBAL ECOSYSTEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">56.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Global ecosystems encompass the broader concept of ecosystems, which can be 'sick' due to imbalances in population dynamics."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-c684cf27cea2ae93283f2376d5fc88d9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ECOSYSTEMS&quot;" target="&quot;ORGANISMS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Ecosystems include organisms and their interactions, which are studied by ecologists."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-86f3f3c15069861d2c2d1799514caa1a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SHARKS&quot;" target="&quot;OCEANS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sharks inhabit the oceans, facing severe population declines in recent decades due to overfishing and habitat destruction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SHARKS&quot;" target="&quot;HUMANITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Humanity's actions, such as overfishing, have caused severe population declines in shark species, threatening their survival."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HABITATS&quot;" target="&quot;POACHING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Habitats can be disturbed by poaching, leading to declines in species populations."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HABITATS&quot;" target="&quot;OVERFISHING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Overfishing can disrupt marine habitats, leading to declines in fish populations."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HABITATS&quot;" target="&quot;ECOLOGISTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Ecologists study habitats to understand the impact of human activities on ecosystem health."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HABITATS&quot;" target="&quot;GLOBAL ECOSYSTEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Global ecosystems are affected by habitat disturbances, leading to overall ecosystem stress."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ECOLOGISTS&quot;" target="&quot;EXTINCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Ecologists work to prevent extinctions by studying and conserving endangered species."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GLOBAL ECOSYSTEMS&quot;" target="&quot;EXTINCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Global ecosystems are threatened by the risk of extinction, which can lead to significant disruptions in ecosystem balance."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ff0a9d87e7bab5a46c0271ec9f135255</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HUMAN POPULATION&quot;" target="&quot;EARTH'S ANNUAL CAPACITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">72.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The growth of the human population has led to increased demand on Earth's annual capacity, causing it to exceed the sustainable limit."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-c684cf27cea2ae93283f2376d5fc88d9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HUMAN POPULATION&quot;" target="&quot;TOTAL ECOLOGICAL FOOTPRINT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">153.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The growth of the human population has directly contributed to the expansion of the total ecological footprint, leading to the current overshoot condition."&lt;SEP&gt;"The total ecological footprint is a direct result of human population activities, such as agriculture and resource extraction, which have contributed to the current overshoot."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-c684cf27cea2ae93283f2376d5fc88d9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARTH'S ANNUAL CAPACITY&quot;" target="&quot;TOTAL ECOLOGICAL FOOTPRINT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">56.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"As the total ecological footprint increases, it puts pressure on Earth's annual capacity, leading to an overshoot condition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-c684cf27cea2ae93283f2376d5fc88d9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TOTAL ECOLOGICAL FOOTPRINT&quot;" target="&quot;FIGURE 2&quot;">
  <data key="d4">64.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Figure 2 visually represents the relationship between humanity's ecological demands and the Earth's production capacity, highlighting the increasing overshoot."</data>
