  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Ecological overshoot occurs due to the unsustainable practices of the human economy."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-86f3f3c15069861d2c2d1799514caa1a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ANIMALS&quot;" target="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Viral oncogenes have been discovered in various animals, including chickens, mice, and rats, highlighting their presence across different species."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ANIMALS&quot;" target="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cellular proto-oncogenes are found in animals, including humans, suggesting a common genetic basis for cancer across species."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BODY ORGANS AND TISSUES&quot;" target="&quot;ORGANISMS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Organisms have body organs and tissues that are studied by physiologists."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-86f3f3c15069861d2c2d1799514caa1a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHYSIOLOGICAL REGULATION&quot;" target="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Studying bacteria was the first breakthrough in understanding physiological regulation, providing general rules applicable to all organisms including humans."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHYSIOLOGICAL REGULATION&quot;" target="&quot;FRANÇOIS JACOB&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"François Jacob's description of the 'logic' of life provides a framework for understanding the general rules of physiological regulation, enhancing appreciation for how life works."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;" target="&quot;ORGANISMS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bacteria are a type of organism that can be studied by both ecologists and physiologists."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-86f3f3c15069861d2c2d1799514caa1a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;" target="&quot;FRANÇOIS JACOB&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"François Jacob's work on the 'logic' of life was inspired by the pioneering research on bacteria, highlighting the importance of these microorganisms in understanding physiological regulation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The pioneering work on bacteria by François Jacob laid the foundation for understanding the general rules of physiological regulation, influencing his later work and descriptions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;" target="&quot;CHOLESTEROL METABOLISM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"General rules discovered in bacteria apply to cholesterol metabolism, enabling the cracking of specific rules for human physiology."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;" target="&quot;CELL GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"General rules discovered in bacteria also apply to cell growth, contributing to the understanding of specific rules in human physiology."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;" target="&quot;HUMANS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both bacteria and humans have complex systems that can be regulated."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-ffea4d43ecf72d0e1bf7106003d38157</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FRANÇOIS JACOB&quot;" target="&quot;CANNON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cannon discusses the adaptability of cells, similar to the logic highlighted by François Jacob in his work."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e565e66ef834e4caca689e27371f4bd5</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHOLESTEROL METABOLISM&quot;" target="&quot;CELL GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Understanding Cholesterol metabolism and cell growth are interconnected aspects of physiological regulation, both benefiting from the general rules discovered in bacteria."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PIONEERING WORK&quot;" target="&quot;GENERAL RULES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pioneering work on bacteria led to the discovery of general rules of physiological regulation, which are fundamental to understanding specific rules in various physiological processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SPECIFIC RULES&quot;" target="&quot;GENERAL RULES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"General rules provide the basis for understanding specific rules in physiological processes, such as cholesterol metabolism and cell growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GENERAL RULES&quot;" target="&quot;ORGANISM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"General rules apply to all organisms, from simple bacteria to complex multicellular organisms, governing their physiological processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d106303a552d91d638c6109b9cbc3308</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANNON&quot;" target="&quot;SHOCK IN WOUNDED SOLDIERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cannon recognized shock symptoms in wounded soldiers and conducted experiments to understand and mitigate the syndrome."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f57af36635a6b8ade4cbaf6b9d73c825</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
