<edge source="&quot;RSV&quot;" target="&quot;VARMUS AND BISHOP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Varmus and Bishop studied RSV as part of their research on tumor viruses at UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RSV&quot;" target="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">17.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"RSV was one of the specific tumor viruses studied by Varmus and Bishop at UCSF, contributing to their broader research on tumor viruses."&lt;SEP&gt;"The study of RSV at UCSF, including the work of Varmus and Bishop, provided insights into the mechanisms of tumor viruses and the _src_ gene, highlighting the importance of viral infection and replication mechanisms in understanding tumor viruses."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RSV&quot;" target="&quot;C- _SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The study of RSV at UCSF contributed to the understanding of the c- _src_ gene and its role in cellular processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RSV&quot;" target="&quot;GENETIC ENGINEERING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The study of RSV at UCSF, including the work of Varmus and Bishop, utilized genetic engineering techniques to understand the _src_ gene and its role in cellular processes, highlighting the importance of genetic engineering in advancing scientific knowledge."&lt;SEP&gt;"The study of RSV at UCSF, including the work of Varmus and Bishop, utilized genetic engineering techniques to understand the _src_ gene and its role in cellular processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RSV&quot;" target="&quot;CELLULAR REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The study of RSV at UCSF, including the work of Varmus and Bishop, provided insights into the mechanisms of cellular regulation and the _src_ gene, highlighting the importance of viral infection and replication mechanisms in understanding cellular regulation and tumor viruses."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RSV&quot;" target="&quot;VIRAL INFECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The study of RSV at UCSF, including the work of Varmus and Bishop, provided insights into the mechanisms of viral infection and the _src_ gene, highlighting the importance of viral infection and replication mechanisms in understanding tumor viruses and the _src_ gene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RSV&quot;" target="&quot;V- _SRC_&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"RSV can acquire the v- _src_ gene by hijacking a copy of the c- _src_ gene, altering it to cause cancerous growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;VARMUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Varmus conducted his early research on enzyme regulation systems at NIH before moving to UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;BISHOP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bishop's initial research on the polio virus was conducted at NIH before he moved to UCSF with Varmus."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;C- _SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The discovery of the c- _src_ gene was a result of research initially conducted at NIH, where Varmus worked on enzyme regulation systems."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;GENETIC ENGINEERING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The research conducted at NIH, including Varmus's work on enzyme regulation systems, contributed to the development of genetic engineering techniques that were later used by Varmus and Bishop at UCSF to study the _src_ gene and its role in cellular processes."&lt;SEP&gt;"The research conducted at NIH, including Varmus's work on enzyme regulation systems, contributed to the development of genetic engineering techniques that were later used by Varmus and Bishop at UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The research conducted at NIH, including Varmus's work on enzyme regulation systems, contributed to the understanding of tumor viruses and the _src_ gene, as later pursued by Varmus and Bishop at UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;CELLULAR REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The research conducted at NIH, including Varmus's work on enzyme regulation systems, contributed to the understanding of cellular regulation and the _src_ gene, as later pursued by Varmus and Bishop at UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;VIRAL INFECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The research conducted at NIH, including Varmus's work on enzyme regulation systems, contributed to the understanding of viral infection and the _src_ gene, as later pursued by Varmus and Bishop at UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NIH&quot;" target="&quot;REPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The research conducted at NIH, including Varmus's work on enzyme regulation systems, contributed to the understanding of viral replication and the _src_ gene, as later pursued by Varmus and Bishop at UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MONOD AND JACOB&quot;" target="&quot;VARMUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Varmus was influenced by the work of Monod and Jacob on enzyme regulation systems during his time at NIH."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MONOD AND JACOB&quot;" target="&quot;JANET ROWLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Monod and Jacob's work inspired Janet Rowley to break the rules of regulation and investigate the consequences, leading to her breakthrough in cancer research."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2fb209d4d4b002a2738060d2c88fd01f</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MONOD AND JACOB&quot;" target="&quot;BREAKING THE RULES OF REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Monod and Jacob's work inspired Janet Rowley to break the rules of regulation and investigate the consequences."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2fb209d4d4b002a2738060d2c88fd01f</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MONOD AND JACOB&quot;" target="&quot;CONSTITUTIVE MUTANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Monod and Jacob studied constitutive mutants, which are always active, similar to the bcr/abl fusion protein."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4808624bb772962b1d285e9a96aaec01</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;POLIO VIRUS&quot;" target="&quot;BISHOP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bishop's initial research focused on the polio virus before he began studying tumor viruses with Varmus."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME REGULATION SYSTEM&quot;" target="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The discovery of the _src_ gene highlighted the importance of enzyme regulation systems in cellular processes, which was a topic of interest for both Varmus and Bishop."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;" target="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The _src_ gene was a key focus of Varmus and Bishop's research on tumor viruses, as it played a significant role in understanding the mechanisms of viral infection and replication."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;" target="&quot;C- _SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The c- _src_ gene, found in normal cells, was studied by Varmus and Bishop in relation to tumor viruses, highlighting its potential role in cellular processes and viral infection mechanisms."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;" target="&quot;V- _SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The v- _src_ gene, found in viruses, was studied by Varmus and Bishop in relation to tumor viruses, providing insights into the mechanisms of viral infection and replication."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;" target="&quot;GENETIC ENGINEERING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Genetic engineering techniques were essential for understanding the _src_ gene and its role in tumor viruses, as demonstrated by the work of Varmus and Bishop at UCSF."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;" target="&quot;UCSF&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The research conducted at UCSF, including the work of Varmus and Bishop on the _src_ gene, advanced the field of understanding tumor viruses and their mechanisms of infection and replication."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;" target="&quot;TUMOR VIRUS ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Tumor viruses, such as those infecting chickens, mice, or rats, were found to contain oncogenes with cellular counterparts."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;" target="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Tumor viruses contain viral oncogenes that can cause cancer in animals, establishing a clear link between the two."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VARMUS&quot;" target="&quot;BISHOP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Varmus and Bishop collaborated on the study of tumor viruses at UCSF after Varmus joined Bishop's laboratory in 1970."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VARMUS&quot;" target="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Varmus's research at NIH laid the groundwork for his later studies on the _src_ gene and its implications for tumor viruses."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VARMUS&quot;" target="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Varmus and Bishop discovered the c- _src_ gene in mammals, including humans."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;VARMUS AND BISHOP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Varmus and Bishop were intrigued by the _src_ gene and wondered about its origin after its discovery."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;C- _SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The discovery of the c- _src_ gene confirmed the existence of a similar gene in normal chicken cells, distinguishing it from the viral version of the gene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;V- _SRC_ GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The _src_ gene found in viruses is distinct from the c- _src_ gene found in normal cells, prompting further investigation into their origins and functions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;BISHOP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bishop's expertise in virology contributed to the understanding of the _src_ gene and its role in cellular processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;GENETIC ENGINEERING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The discovery of the _src_ gene and the subsequent experiments to confirm its presence in chicken cells were made possible by advancements in genetic engineering techniques."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;CELLULAR PROCESSES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The _src_ gene plays a crucial role in cellular processes, which was a key area of interest for Varmus and Bishop in their research on tumor viruses and the _src_ gene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;CELLULAR REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The _src_ gene is involved in cellular regulation, which was a key area of interest for Varmus and Bishop in their research on tumor viruses and the _src_ gene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;VIRAL INFECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The _src_ gene is involved in viral infection, which was a key focus of Varmus and Bishop's research on tumor viruses and the _src_ gene, as it played a significant role in understanding the mechanisms of viral infection and replication."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;_SRC_ GENE&quot;" target="&quot;REPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The _src_ gene is involved in the replication of viruses, which was a key focus of Varmus and Bishop's research on tumor viruses and the _src_ gene, as it played a significant role in understanding the mechanisms of viral infection and replication."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DOMINIQUE STEHELIN&quot;" target="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dominique Stehelin obtained evidence of the c- _src_ gene in chicken cells in October 1974."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DOMINIQUE STEHELIN&quot;" target="&quot;OCTOBER 1974&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dominique Stehelin obtained evidence of the similar src gene in chicken cells in October 1974."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;V- _SRC_&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"c- _src_ and v- _src_ are closely related genes, with v- _src_ causing cancerous growth when altered."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;BISHOP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bishop and Varmus discovered the c- _src_ gene in mammals and pondered its implications."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;DEBORAH SPECTOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Deborah Spector helped discover the c- _src_ gene in mammals."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;TUMOR VIRUS ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Tumor virus oncogenes, such as v- _src_, are closely related to the cellular c- _src_ gene and can cause cancerous growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;CHICKEN CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The c- _src_ gene was initially discovered in chicken cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;MAMMALS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The c- _src_ gene was found in mammals, including humans, indicating its ancient evolutionary origin."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;BIRDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The c- _src_ gene was found in various birds, including chickens, ducks, turkeys, and emus, showing its presence across different avian species."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;EMUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Emus were found to have the c- _src_ gene, showing its presence across different avian species."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;DUCKS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Ducks were found to have the c- _src_ gene, showing its presence across different avian species."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;TURKEYS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Turkeys were found to have the c- _src_ gene, showing its presence across different avian species."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;CHICKENS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chickens were the initial source where the c- _src_ gene was discovered."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;NORMAL CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The c- _src_ gene is present in normal cells and performs its normal function without causing cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;CELLULAR COUNTERPARTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cellular counterparts refer to the normal cellular genes that are similar to the oncogenes found in tumor viruses."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;C- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;EVOLUTIONARY PEDIGREE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The evolutionary pedigree of c- _src_ indicates its importance in normal cell functions and its ancient origin."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;V- _SRC_&quot;" target="&quot;TUMOR-CAUSING RSV&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Tumor-causing RSV can acquire the v- _src_ gene by hijacking a copy of the c- _src_ gene, altering it to cause cancerous growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BISHOP&quot;" target="&quot;UCSF&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bishop was already working at UCSF when Varmus joined his laboratory in 1970 to study tumor viruses."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fd713c1707a1bad14d6734385a8f1f12</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUS ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;DIFFERENT TUMOR VIRUSES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Different tumor viruses, such as those infecting chickens, mice, or rats, contain oncogenes with cellular counterparts."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUS ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;MICE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mice were found to have tumor virus oncogenes with cellular counterparts, indicating their relevance in the study."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TUMOR VIRUS ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;RATS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Rats were found to have tumor virus oncogenes with cellular counterparts, indicating their relevance in the study."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9f930625fef3887e1239741ea034e7bc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Viral oncogenes are derived from normal cellular genes called proto-oncogenes, indicating a direct relationship between these concepts."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;MYC GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"MYC gene can be found in tumor viruses as a viral oncogene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;ABL GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"ABL gene can be found in tumor viruses as a viral oncogene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;RAS GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"RAS gene can be found in tumor viruses as a viral oncogene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIRAL ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;CHROMOSOMAL CHANGES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chromosomal changes are often associated with the presence of viral oncogenes and can indicate cancer development."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;HUMAN C&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Research into human c suggests an ongoing investigation into the genetic basis of cancer, involving cellular proto-oncogenes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;MYC GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"MYC gene is a specific type of cellular proto-oncogene that can become an oncogene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;ABL GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"ABL gene is a specific type of cellular proto-oncogene that can become an oncogene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;RAS GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"RAS gene is a specific type of cellular proto-oncogene that can become an oncogene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CELLULAR PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;CHROMOSOMAL CHANGES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chromosomal changes can affect cellular proto-oncogenes, turning them into oncogenes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIRUS RESEARCH&quot;" target="&quot;RESEARCHERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Virus research is conducted by researchers to understand the role of viral oncogenes and cellular proto-oncogenes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CANCER RESEARCH&quot;" target="&quot;RESEARCHERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cancer research is conducted by researchers to understand the genetic and molecular basis of cancer, including viral oncogenes and cellular proto-oncogenes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GENETIC MATERIAL&quot;" target="&quot;CHROMOSOMES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Genetic material is carried by chromosomes, which are studied in relation to cancer and viral oncogenes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHROMOSOMES&quot;" target="&quot;JANET ROWLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chromosomes are the focus of Janet Rowley's research, contributing to her understanding of cancer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2fb209d4d4b002a2738060d2c88fd01f</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MUTATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mutations in proto-oncogenes can turn them into oncogenes, contributing to cancer development."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PROTO-ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;ONCOGENES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Proto-oncogenes can become oncogenes when mutated, contributing to cancer development."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ONCOGENES&quot;" target="&quot;CANCER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Oncogenes contribute to cancer development, often derived from normal proto-oncogenes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5a3865eb058f0b3cc7bdbd824f201bd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
