  <data key="d5">"The Breath is the power source that sets the vocal folds in motion, essential for the production of the singing voice."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL SYSTEM&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vocal Folds are the vibrators that produce sound when set in motion by the breath, crucial for the singing voice."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BREATH&quot;" target="&quot;VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Voice involves using Breath to power the vocal folds during speech."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;WARM-UPS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Warm-ups prepare the vocal folds for use through various exercises and techniques."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a51071d5167d43f8855eef4ba001dbe8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;COOL-DOWNS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cool-downs help the vocal folds recover from use during singing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a51071d5167d43f8855eef4ba001dbe8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL WARM-UPS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vocal Warm-ups prepare the vocal folds for use through various exercises and techniques."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a51071d5167d43f8855eef4ba001dbe8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;SYSTEMIC HYDRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Systemic Hydration is crucial for keeping the Vocal Folds adequately lubricated to handle the impact and friction they experience during use."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;MUCUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mucus is produced by the body and can affect the function of the Vocal Folds if it becomes thick and sticky."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;PHONOTRAUMA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Phonotrauma can compromise the integrity of the Vibration Patterns of the Vocal Folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;MALE SPEAKING FREQUENCY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Male Speaking Frequency ranges from 100 to 150 Hz and is important for understanding the behavior of the Vocal Folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;FEMALE SPEAKING FREQUENCY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Female Speaking Frequency ranges from 180 to 230 Hz and is important for understanding the behavior of the Vocal Folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">34.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Phonotraumatic Behaviors can cause damage to the Vocal Folds."&lt;SEP&gt;"Phonotraumatic behaviors can cause damage to the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;GOOD HYDRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Good Hydration ensures the Vocal Folds remain lubricated and functional."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;IMPACT AND FRICTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Impact and Friction refer to the forces experienced by the Vocal Folds during use."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLD VIBRATION PATTERNS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vocal Fold Vibration Patterns are the specific ways in which the Vocal Folds vibrate to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;LUBRICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Lubrication is necessary for the proper functioning of the Vocal Folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;MEMBRANES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Membranes are part of the Vocal Folds and require proper hydration."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;" target="&quot;GOOD VOCAL HEALTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Good vocal health is maintained by avoiding phonotraumatic behaviors."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Voice involves enhancing Resonance to make the sound full and rich."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FIELD BEES&quot;" target="&quot;LOAD OF NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">27.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Field bees collect nectar and bring it back to the hive, passing it off to house bees for further processing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5e1db9c56d4738764f06ecc0b5763c66</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVEMATES&quot;" target="&quot;DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hivemates interpret the Dance to gather information about the new food source."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVEMATES&quot;" target="&quot;ANTENNAE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hivemates use Antennae to follow the Dancer and gather information about the new food source."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foragers perform the Round Dance after returning to the Hive with a sample of Nectar."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both dances are used by bees to communicate the discovery of nectar sources, but the Wag-Tail Dance provides more detailed information compared to the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Forager Bees perform the Round Dance to communicate the location of nectar sources within 100 meters of the Hive."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;SAMPLE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Samples of nectar or pollen are offered during the Round Dance to indicate the type of forage discovered."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;ODOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Odors adhering to the dancer's body during the Round Dance can indicate the type of forage discovered."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;RANDOM SEARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees perform a random search within the 100-meter radius indicated by the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;NEW SOURCE OF NECTAR OR POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Round Dance is performed to signal the discovery of a new source of nectar or pollen within 100 meters of the hive."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;SAMPLE OF NECTAR OR POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Samples of nectar or pollen are offered during the Round Dance to indicate the type of forage discovered."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;ODOR ADHERING TO DANCER'S BODY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Odors adhering to the dancer's body during the Round Dance can indicate the type of forage discovered."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ROUND DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;RANDOM SEARCH AREA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees perform a random search within the 100-meter radius indicated by the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foragers perform the Wag-Tail Dance after returning to the Hive with a sample of Nectar."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FORAGER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Forager Bees perform the Wag-Tail Dance to communicate the precise location of nectar sources more than 100 meters away."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;SUN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The orientation of the figure-eight pattern in the Wag-Tail Dance is related to the direction of the sun, helping bees interpret the direction to the nectar source."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FIGURE-EIGHT PATTERN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Figure-Eight Pattern in the Wag-Tail Dance conveys both the distance and direction of the nectar source."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;DISTANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance conveys the precise distance to the nectar source, providing more accurate information than the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;DIRECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance conveys the direction to the nectar source using the orientation of the figure-eight pattern relative to the sun."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;PRECISION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance provides more precise information than the Round Dance, conveying both distance and direction."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;MARGIN OF ERROR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance conveys information within a relatively small margin of error, making it more accurate than the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;PRECISE DISTANCE RANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance is used to convey precise distance information for sources more than 100 meters from the hive."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;DIRECTION OF SUN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The orientation of the figure-eight pattern in the Wag-Tail Dance is related to the direction of the sun."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;DIRECTION INFORMATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance conveys the direction to the nectar source using the orientation of the figure-eight pattern relative to the sun."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;DISTANCE INFORMATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Wag-Tail Dance conveys the precise distance to the nectar source, providing more accurate information than the Round Dance."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FIGURE-EIGHT PATTERN IN WAG-TAIL DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use the Figure-Eight Pattern in the Wag-Tail Dance to convey information about the nectar source."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-53ba801aab88a318b172032db00d5a26</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORAGER&quot;" target="&quot;DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foragers perform the Dance after returning to the Hive with a sample of Nectar."&lt;SEP&gt;"Foragers perform the Dance to communicate the location of new food sources to their Hivemates."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORAGER&quot;" target="&quot;SAMPLE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foragers bring back a Sample of the nectar to communicate the location of the food source."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9e973cd1cc5f8803251af14f60c371c6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DANCE&quot;" target="&quot;VERTICAL SURFACE OF THE COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
