  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Philadelphia chromosome involves a translocation on chromosome 9, implicating it in CML."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d0cf0b37864347226f145a22592586fb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHILADELPHIA CHROMOSOME&quot;" target="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">34.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Philadelphia chromosome results from a translocation event."&lt;SEP&gt;"Translocation is a key characteristic of the Philadelphia chromosome, involving the movement of the c-ABL gene to chromosome 22."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5a1c664c094403842e858c8931bde7c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0cf0b37864347226f145a22592586fb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHILADELPHIA CHROMOSOME&quot;" target="&quot;DUTCH AND BRITISH RESEARCHERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Dutch and British researchers studied the Philadelphia chromosome and discovered the translocation of the c-ABL gene to chromosome 22."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5a1c664c094403842e858c8931bde7c3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHILADELPHIA CHROMOSOME&quot;" target="&quot;CML CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Philadelphia chromosome is a hallmark of CML cells, characterized by the translocation of the c-ABL gene to chromosome 22 and the fusion with the bcr gene."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5a1c664c094403842e858c8931bde7c3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHROMOSOME 9&quot;" target="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Translocation involves chromosome 9, specifically the c- _abl_ gene on chromosome 9."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d0cf0b37864347226f145a22592586fb</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHROMOSOME 9&quot;" target="&quot;C-ABL GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The c-ABL gene is normally located on chromosome 9 but was found to have moved to chromosome 22 in patients with CML."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5a1c664c094403842e858c8931bde7c3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;C-ABL GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The c-ABL gene undergoes translocation from chromosome 9 to chromosome 22 during the formation of the Philadelphia chromosome."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5a1c664c094403842e858c8931bde7c3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TRANSLOCATION&quot;" target="&quot;BCR GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The bcr gene is involved in the translocation process, fusing with the c-ABL gene on chromosome 22."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5a1c664c094403842e858c8931bde7c3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
