  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MEDICATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;MUCUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Medications can potentially dry the membranes and should be minimized to maintain proper hydration."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DRY AIR&quot;" target="&quot;MUCUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Dry Air can contribute to dehydration and should be minimized to maintain proper hydration."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MUCUS&quot;" target="&quot;THICK AND STICKY MUCUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Thick and Sticky Mucus is a condition where Mucus becomes viscous and less effective in lubricating the Vocal Folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONOTRAUMA&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL BEHAVIORS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vocal Behaviors such as yelling and screaming can lead to Phonotrauma."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;" target="&quot;YELLING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Yelling is a type of phonotraumatic behavior."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;" target="&quot;SCREAMING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Screaming is a type of phonotraumatic behavior."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;" target="&quot;LOUD TALKING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Loud talking is a type of phonotraumatic behavior."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;" target="&quot;HARSH SNEEZING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Harsh sneezing is a type of phonotraumatic behavior."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;" target="&quot;HARSH LAUGHING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Harsh laughing is a type of phonotraumatic behavior."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONOTRAUMATIC BEHAVIORS&quot;" target="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Laryngeal impact injuries can result from phonotraumatic behaviors."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EFFICIENT AND EFFECTIVE VOICE PRODUCTION&quot;" target="&quot;VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Efficient and Effective Voice Production involves producing clear and strong sounds without strain."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOICE&quot;" target="&quot;FREQUENCY RANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Voice involves optimizing Frequency Range for effective communication."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOICE&quot;" target="&quot;RATE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Voice involves managing Rate to control the speed of speech."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENGINE EFFICIENCY&quot;" target="&quot;OIL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Engine Efficiency is improved by using Oil to reduce friction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENGINE EFFICIENCY&quot;" target="&quot;GEARS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Gears transfer power and motion in an Engine, affecting its efficiency."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENGINE EFFICIENCY&quot;" target="&quot;HEAT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Heat is a byproduct of friction in an Engine, affecting its efficiency."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OIL&quot;" target="&quot;LUBRICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Oil is used for Lubrication to reduce friction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MICROSTRUCTURE&quot;" target="&quot;LUBRICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Microstructure is the detailed structure of the Vocal Folds, which requires proper Lubrication."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYDRATION LEVELS&quot;" target="&quot;MEMBRANES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hydration Levels affect the Membranes lining the Vocal Folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-48744b276bffa8148a6398e5afebc9e2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL INTENSITY&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS IMPACT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Increased vocal intensity leads to harder impacts on the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS IMPACT&quot;" target="&quot;A3&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"At A3, the vocal folds vibrate at 220 times per second, creating a certain level of impact."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS IMPACT&quot;" target="&quot;A4&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"At A4, the vocal folds vibrate at 440 times per second, increasing the impact."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS IMPACT&quot;" target="&quot;A5&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"At A5, the vocal folds vibrate at 880 times per second, further increasing the impact."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS IMPACT&quot;" target="&quot;HIGH C&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Singing a high C involves more than 1,000 vibrations per second, significantly increasing the impact on the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS IMPACT&quot;" target="&quot;SIX INCHES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"At six inches, the impact on the vocal folds is significant but manageable."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS IMPACT&quot;" target="&quot;TWO FEET&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"At two feet, the impact on the vocal folds is even more significant."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WOMEN&quot;" target="&quot;MEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Women are more prone to laryngeal impact injuries due to the frequency range of their voices compared to men."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WOMEN&quot;" target="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Women are more prone to laryngeal impact injuries than men, possibly due to physiological differences in voice frequency range."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a2c0af1587a2184c200ca24db4ff8502</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MEN&quot;" target="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Men are less prone to laryngeal impact injuries compared to women, suggesting different physiological characteristics."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a2c0af1587a2184c200ca24db4ff8502</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RED AND SWOLLEN SKIN&quot;" target="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Red and swollen skin is a symptom of laryngeal impact injuries."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;" target="&quot;TESSITURA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Singing in a high tessitura for prolonged periods can increase the risk of laryngeal impact injuries due to muscle strain."&lt;SEP&gt;"Women are more prone to laryngeal impact injuries due to the frequency range of their voices, which affects their tessitura."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a2c0af1587a2184c200ca24db4ff8502&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;" target="&quot;FREQUENCY RANGE OF THE VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The frequency range of the voice can influence the likelihood of laryngeal impact injuries."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f048b0415055a67eb6c616d2e3dadcb3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;" target="&quot;MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Muscles, particularly those involved in vocalization, can be strained or injured, leading to laryngeal impact injuries."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a2c0af1587a2184c200ca24db4ff8502</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNGEAL IMPACT INJURIES&quot;" target="&quot;CYCLES PER SEC&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The frequency of sound waves (cycles per second) can affect the strain on vocal muscles, contributing to the risk of laryngeal impact injuries."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a2c0af1587a2184c200ca24db4ff8502</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;SWARM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A swarm represents a new beginning for both the swarm and the parent colony that casts it."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7c6b4aa8d243f96f198f44c125be2f03</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
